cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PF, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on estimating workload execution characteristics on distributed heterogeneous resources.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper introduces an automated and system-independent application profiler.
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to improve workload placement by accurately predicting application characteristics.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) may be relevant as the paper deals with distributed resources and workload placement.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) may also be relevant as the paper introduces a system for workload emulation and placement.
